body:
Related to #1743. When using the max_and_skip wrapper with an env and the ray_sampler, the private field of the wrapper `self._obs_buffer` is not pickled properly. When ray workers go to write to this buffer, which is a numpy array, they get the error because `self._obs_buffer` is now read only. 

I don't believe that generally numpy arrays need to be pickled in special ways -- we do this all the time for policy weights. However, perhaps there is some special logic required to wrap environments that have an underlying numpy array inside of their wrappers.

@krzentner, @ryanjulian wdyt?
